name: AwsALBEvent
desc:
Event send by an Application Load Balancer to the
invocation to the Lambda.

name: body
desc:
Body of the request. This can be data that is send with the POST
to the request.

name: context
desc:
Request context in which this request is executed.
For the ELB this is the ARN of the target group.

name: headers
desc: HTTP headers that are send with the request to the load balancer.

name: httpMethod
desc: HTTP method that is used to trigger the invocation of the Lambda.

name: isBase64Encoded
desc: Singals that the request is Base64 encoded.

name: path
desc: The URI that is accessed to trigger the invocation of the Lambda.

name: queryStringParameters
desc: The query parameters for the request to the load balancer.

name: AwsALBEventContext
desc: AWS ALB Event Request Context ...

name: AwsALBResponse
desc:
Response for a request from an Application Load Balancer.
It has to have a statusCode, headers and a body.
They should reflect the informationen needed here.

name: AwsALBResponse
desc:
The Response that should be returned to the Application Load Balancer.
It is constructed with some default values for the optional parameters.

name: body
desc: The body of the HTTP Response send from the API Gateway to the client.

name: headers
desc: The HTTP headers that should be send with the response to the client.

name: isBase64Encoded
desc: Indicates if the body is Base64 encoded or not. By default is false.

name: statusCode
desc:
HTTP status code of the response of the API Gateway to the client.
The default status code is 200 OK.

name: statusDescription
desc: Description of the send HTTP status code.

name: toJson
desc:
Returns the JSON representation of the response. This is called by
the JSON encoder to produce the response.

name: payload

name: AwsAlexaEventHeader
desc: Header are meta information about the event.

name: name
desc: Name of the event

name: namespace
desc: Namespace of the event.

name: payloadVersion
desc: Version of the send payload.

name: AwsApiGatewayResponse
desc:
API Gateway Response contains the data for a response
to the API Gateway. It contains the body of the HTTP response.
It also contains a HTTP Status Code which by default is 200.
Furthermore it indicates if the body is Base64 encoded or not.

name: AwsApiGatewayResponse
desc:
The Response that should be returned by the API Gateway for the
Lambda invocation. It has a body which reflects the body of the HTTP Response.
But also it signals if the body is Base64 encoded and what the HTTP Status Code
of the response is.

name: AwsApiGatewayResponse.fromJson
desc:
The factory creates a new AwsApiGatewayResponse from JSON.
It optionally accepts the Base64 encoded flag and a HTTP Status Code
for the response.

name: body
desc: The body of the HTTP Response send from the API Gateway to the client.

name: headers
desc: The HTTP headers that should be send with the response to the client.

name: isBase64Encoded
desc: Indicates if the body is Base64 encoded or not. By default is false.

name: toJson
desc:
Returns the JSON representation of the response. This is called by
the JSON encoder to produce the response.

name: Client
desc:
Client is the Lambda Runtime Interface client.
It is implemented as a singleton whereby Client.instance
always returns the already instantiated client.

name: getNextInvocation
desc: Get the next invocation from the AWS Lambda Runtime Interface (see https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/runtimes-api.html).

name: postInvocationError
desc:
Post an invocation error to the AWS Lambda Runtime Interface.
It takes in an InvocationError and the requestId. The requestId
is used to map the error to the execution.

name: postInvocationResponse
desc: Post the invocation response to the AWS Lambda Runtime Interface.

name: InvocationError
desc:
Invocation error occurs when there has been an
error in the invocation of a handlers. It dynamically
wraps the inner error and attaches the requestId to
track it along the event.

name: error
desc:
The error that catched during the invocation and
which is posted to the Lambda Runtime Interface.

name: stackTrace
desc: StackTrace ...

name: toJson
desc:
Extracts the InvocationError data into a JSON
representation for the Runtime Interface.

name: InvocationResult
desc:
Invocation result is the result that the invoked handler
returns and is posted to the Lambda Runtime Interface.

name: body
desc:
The result of the handler execution. This can contain
any json-encodable data type.

name: requestId
desc:
The Id of the request in the Lambda Runtime Interface.
This is used to associate the result of the handler with
the triggered execution in the Runtime.

name: NextInvocation
desc:
Next invocation data wraps the data from the
invocation endpoint of the Lambda Runtime Interface.

name: clientContext
desc: Client context is the context that is provided to the function.

name: cognitoIdentity
desc: Cognito identity is the identity that maybe is used for authorizing the request.

name: deadlineMs
desc: Deadline milliseconds is the setting for ultimate cancelation of the invocation.

name: fromResponse
desc: Digesting a HttpClientResponse into a NextInvocation.

name: invokedFunctionArn
desc: Invoked function ARN is the identifier of the function.

name: requestId
desc: Request Id is the identifier of the request.

name: response
desc: Raw response of invocation data that we received.

name: traceId
desc: Tracing id is the identifier for tracing like X-Ray.

name: Handler
desc:
A function which ingests and Event and a Context
and returns a InvocationResult. The result is ecoded
by the Runtime and posted to the Lambda API.

name: Runtime
desc: A Runtime manages the interface to the Lambda API.

name: deregisterEvent
desc:
Deregister an new event to be ingested by a handler.
The type should reflect your type in your handler definition Handler<T>.

name: deregisterHandler
desc: Unregister a handler function Handler with name.

name: handlerExists
desc:
Checks if a specific handlers has been registered
with the runtime.

name: handlers
desc:
Lists the registered handlers by name.
The name is a simple String which reflects
the name of the trigger in the Lambda Execution API.

name: invoke
desc:
Run the Runtime in loop and digest events that are
fetched from the AWS Lambda API Interface. The events are processed
sequentially and are fetched from the AWS Lambda API Interface.

name: registerEvent
desc:
Register an new event to be ingested by a handler.
The type should reflect your type in your handler definition Handler<T>.

name: registerHandler
desc:
Register a handler function Handler<T> with name
which digests an event T.

name: sequencer
desc: a string representation of a hexadecimal value used to determine event sequence, only used with PUTs and DELETEs

name: size
desc: object-size in bytes

name: versionId
